WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.970 --> 00:00:04.319
<i>Previously on</i> Wayward Pines.

2
00:00:04.388 --> 00:00:07.489
You didn't think Wayward
Pines ran itself. did you?

3
00:00:09.176 --> 00:00:13.929
- Hey. Who are all
of these people?
- Volunteers.

4
00:00:13.998 --> 00:00:16.247
<i>(Pilcher) We were changing
the world. and as a result...</i>

5
00:00:16.316 --> 00:00:19.334
- (Shrieking)
- <i>we ourselves were beginning</i>
<i>to change.</i>

6
00:00:19.403 --> 00:00:21.953
(Snarling)

7
00:00:22.022 --> 00:00:25.490
(Pilcher) Testing cryonic suspension
was both dangerous and illegal.

8
00:00:25.559 --> 00:00:27.337
- (Ethan) They're all asleep.
- (Pilcher) Yes.

9
00:00:27.361 --> 00:00:30.462
This isn't a little town. Ethan.
This is a new civilization.

10
00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:33.632
- <i>(Ethan) You have to</i>
<i>tell them the truth.</i>
- People are fragile.

11
00:00:33.700 --> 00:00:36.085
<i>They need time to adapt.</i>

12
00:00:36.153 --> 00:00:39.137
- Young minds are fearless.
- Welcome to
the first generation.

13
00:00:39.206 --> 00:00:41.773
<i>(Pilcher) They're less
ingrained in the old world.</i>

14
00:00:41.842 --> 00:00:43.642
<i>They can accept the truth.</i>

15
00:00:43.710 --> 00:00:44.943
There's a new threat.

16
00:00:45.012 --> 00:00:46.794
<i>We don't know who they are.</i>

17
00:00:46.863 --> 00:00:49.314
<i>but they're gonna
take down the fence.</i>

18
00:00:49.382 --> 00:00:52.150
- If they succeed...
- They're not going to succeed.

19
00:00:52.218 --> 00:00:53.718
(Winding)

20
00:00:53.788 --> 00:00:55.787
- ♪♪ (Music Box)
- It's ready.

21
00:01:01.928 --> 00:01:05.330
(Pilcher) Ethan. It is
imperative you tell no one...

22
00:01:05.399 --> 00:01:08.533
about what you've seen
and what you've heard.

23
00:01:08.602 --> 00:01:13.338
I believe the survival of
humanity may well be in our hands.

24
00:01:16.443 --> 00:01:17.592
(Parking Brake Clicks)

25
00:01:30.674 --> 00:01:33.675
(Footsteps)

26
00:01:37.414 --> 00:01:41.216
Ethan. When did you get back?

27
00:01:41.285 --> 00:01:43.935
Have you been
sitting here all night?

28
00:01:44.004 --> 00:01:46.304
Please tell me you
found something.

29
00:01:46.373 --> 00:01:48.006
We have got to
get back to Seattle.

30
00:01:48.075 --> 00:01:51.109
I cannot get ahold of anybody.
Mom's surgery is on Wednesday...

31
00:01:51.178 --> 00:01:52.911
Theresa. Theresa.

32
00:01:54.648 --> 00:01:56.548
There is no Seattle.

33
00:01:59.319 --> 00:02:01.619
What are you talking about?

34
00:02:04.692 --> 00:02:06.191
(Sighs)

35
00:02:06.260 --> 00:02:07.759
Look.

36
00:02:08.929 --> 00:02:11.729
When we were pulled
from those car wrecks.

37
00:02:14.184 --> 00:02:16.664
we weren't taken directly here.

38
00:02:17.720 --> 00:02:20.371
We were put into
some kind of a...

39
00:02:21.424 --> 00:02:23.208
suspended animation.

40
00:02:24.528 --> 00:02:26.594
What happened to your arm?

41
00:02:26.663 --> 00:02:29.583
(Exhales) You're
gonna think I'm crazy.

42
00:02:29.967 --> 00:02:32.134
(Sighs) But there's...

43
00:02:33.437 --> 00:02:35.170
these creatures out there.

44
00:02:36.173 --> 00:02:40.141
Monsters. I saw them
with my own eyes.

45
00:02:40.777 --> 00:02:42.677
Cities destroyed.

46
00:02:44.814 --> 00:02:49.167
This... This fake
little town is...

47
00:02:49.236 --> 00:02:51.103
all that's left.

48
00:02:52.873 --> 00:02:55.073
Ethan. what did they do to you?

49
00:02:55.142 --> 00:02:56.641
(Sighs)

50
00:02:56.710 --> 00:02:59.861
What did they do to you? Did
they take you back to the hospital?

51
00:03:01.231 --> 00:03:02.397
No.

52
00:03:02.466 --> 00:03:04.216
I need you to try to remember...

53
00:03:04.285 --> 00:03:07.602
if they did anything to you. if
they injected you with something.

54
00:03:07.671 --> 00:03:09.115
- You don't believe me.
- Are you sure?

55
00:03:09.139 --> 00:03:10.789
I wasn't at the hospital.

56
00:03:17.213 --> 00:03:20.715
(Sighs) 4028. What...
Okay. what does this mean?

57
00:03:21.818 --> 00:03:23.768
That's the date.

58
00:03:25.489 --> 00:03:27.222
Oh. Ethan.

59
00:03:33.864 --> 00:03:35.964
(Buzzing)

60
00:03:36.033 --> 00:03:37.749
(Beeping)

61
00:03:37.818 --> 00:03:38.984
(Buzzing. Beeping Stop)

62
00:03:40.553 --> 00:03:42.037
What's wrong?

63
00:03:44.625 --> 00:03:46.341
It's the starter.

64
00:03:47.778 --> 00:03:50.218
This might take a while.
You guys should walk.

65
00:03:52.015 --> 00:03:55.183
Okay. Sure.

66
00:03:55.885 --> 00:03:57.385
Let's go.

67
00:04:01.108 --> 00:04:02.908
(Theresa Whispering)
Oh. sorry. sorry.

68
00:04:51.991 --> 00:04:53.158
(Exhales)

69
00:06:27.370 --> 00:06:28.553
(Door Opens)

70
00:06:29.322 --> 00:06:32.089
Good morning. Mr. Burke.

71
00:06:32.159 --> 00:06:34.203
Can I help you with
something. Pam?

72
00:06:34.227 --> 00:06:37.628
No. but I think I can
help<i> you</i> with something.

73
00:06:37.697 --> 00:06:39.814
Really?

74
00:06:40.767 --> 00:06:44.135
Oh. Franklin Dobbs.

75
00:06:44.204 --> 00:06:47.121
Do you think he's involved
with these subversives?

76
00:06:47.891 --> 00:06:49.791
I don't know.

77
00:06:49.860 --> 00:06:52.360
But when I find out the
answer to that question.

78
00:06:52.428 --> 00:06:54.445
you'll be the first to know.

79
00:06:54.514 --> 00:06:58.132
Until then. I've gotta do my
job. so... if you don't mind...

80
00:06:58.201 --> 00:07:00.936
No. I don't mind. Go
ahead. Do your job.

81
00:07:01.004 --> 00:07:02.921
I'm just here to help.

82
00:07:04.290 --> 00:07:07.325
(Sighs) I would do
anything for my brother.

83
00:07:07.394 --> 00:07:10.511
Even work hand-in-hand with you.

84
00:07:10.580 --> 00:07:14.916
So how about it? You can't do
this alone. You need some help?

85
00:07:14.985 --> 00:07:18.019
I can be a very good friend.

86
00:07:21.374 --> 00:07:24.292
How about giving me access
to the surveillance system.

87
00:07:24.360 --> 00:07:27.061
so I can see what
Franklin's been up to?

88
00:07:30.683 --> 00:07:34.619
So. I kinda thought we
had moved past this whole...

89
00:07:34.687 --> 00:07:36.687
walk-your-kid-to-school thing.

90
00:07:38.058 --> 00:07:40.970
I just want to spend time
with you. if that's all right.

91
00:07:40.994 --> 00:07:42.710
(Children Shouting. Distant)

92
00:07:43.830 --> 00:07:46.130
Everything okay?

93
00:07:46.199 --> 00:07:48.549
Yeah.

94
00:07:49.570 --> 00:07:51.370
You ever miss Seattle?

95
00:07:53.073 --> 00:07:54.906
I don't really think about it.

96
00:07:54.974 --> 00:07:58.476
Really? Not even camping...

97
00:07:58.545 --> 00:08:00.739
with your cousins. or
playing with Stanley?

98
00:08:00.763 --> 00:08:02.630
(Chuckles) Stanley.

99
00:08:03.700 --> 00:08:05.800
We're not supposed
to think about the past.

100
00:08:06.937 --> 00:08:08.836
Right.

101
00:08:08.905 --> 00:08:11.039
Good morning.

102
00:08:11.107 --> 00:08:13.153
Good morning. Dr. Jenkins.

103
00:08:13.177 --> 00:08:15.843
(Chattering)

104
00:08:15.912 --> 00:08:18.547
(Laughing) Hey.

105
00:08:18.615 --> 00:08:22.717
I like it here. Mom. I
have friends. I like school.

106
00:08:24.020 --> 00:08:27.021
You'd probably like it too
if you gave it half a chance.

107
00:08:27.090 --> 00:08:30.530
Okay. well. I'm glad things
are working out for you.

108
00:08:31.411 --> 00:08:34.912
Good morning. guys. Nice to see
you. Theresa. (Whispering) Morning.

109
00:08:34.981 --> 00:08:38.099
Hi. Hey. Ben. Mrs. Burke.

110
00:08:38.167 --> 00:08:41.503
Amy. will you help Ben
find a biology textbook?

111
00:08:41.571 --> 00:08:45.089
- There's a big stack of them
behind my desk.
- Yeah. sure. Come on.

112
00:08:47.327 --> 00:08:50.545
You know. I have not set foot
inside that school or your classroom.

113
00:08:50.613 --> 00:08:53.309
Is there a tour or a parent-teacher
conference coming up...

114
00:08:53.333 --> 00:08:57.068
School is for children.
Theresa. not their parents.

115
00:08:57.137 --> 00:09:00.471
Your job is to feed them
and keep them safe.

116
00:09:00.540 --> 00:09:02.773
Let us do the rest.
(School Bell Rings)

117
00:09:02.842 --> 00:09:05.810
Oh! That's my cue.
Nice to see you.

118
00:09:08.982 --> 00:09:11.483
(Ben) Yeah. it looks really bad.

119
00:09:12.619 --> 00:09:15.120
(Students Chattering. Laughing)

120
00:09:52.959 --> 00:09:54.625
(Thunking)

121
00:09:55.912 --> 00:09:58.846
(Thunking)

122
00:10:00.700 --> 00:10:04.319
(Thunking)

123
00:10:32.248 --> 00:10:33.814
(Clank)

124
00:10:36.018 --> 00:10:37.518
(Clank)

125
00:10:46.196 --> 00:10:48.462
I want to thank you for
coming down. Franklin.

126
00:10:48.531 --> 00:10:50.665
As the new sheriff in town.

127
00:10:50.733 --> 00:10:54.803
I'm making a point of getting to know
all the shopkeepers on Main Street.

128
00:10:54.871 --> 00:10:59.541
Never really had a get-to-know-you
meeting with Sheriff Pope.

129
00:11:03.246 --> 00:11:07.364
Franklin. we don't talk
about the past here.

130
00:11:07.433 --> 00:11:09.851
You know that.

131
00:11:09.919 --> 00:11:12.820
(Groans) (Chuckling)
Lighten up. Franklin.

132
00:11:12.889 --> 00:11:14.772
I'm just messin' with ya.

133
00:11:14.841 --> 00:11:18.059
(Chuckles) Oh. But listen.
I did have something...

134
00:11:18.128 --> 00:11:21.929
of a personal nature that
I'd like to discuss with you.

135
00:11:24.734 --> 00:11:26.734
Gophers.

136
00:11:27.904 --> 00:11:30.004
Gophers? Yeah. that's right.

137
00:11:30.073 --> 00:11:32.840
They're destroying my lawn.

138
00:11:32.909 --> 00:11:35.164
And I remember
looking through your file

139
00:11:35.188 --> 00:11:37.695
one day. and it said
that you worked in. uh.

140
00:11:37.763 --> 00:11:40.047
explosive demolition.

141
00:11:41.751 --> 00:11:43.351
Oh.

142
00:11:46.339 --> 00:11:50.708
Afraid I... can't
help you. Sheriff.

143
00:11:50.777 --> 00:11:53.761
Yeah. I should really be
getting back to the shop.

144
00:11:54.330 --> 00:11:55.830
So...

145
00:11:59.519 --> 00:12:01.001
(Door Opens)

146
00:12:03.373 --> 00:12:04.533
(Door Closes)

147
00:12:16.469 --> 00:12:18.652
(Megan) Open your
books to page 17.

148
00:12:21.541 --> 00:12:26.660
- Go ahead and look at
all the pictures.
- (Students Giggling)

149
00:12:26.729 --> 00:12:29.464
Giggle if you want.

150
00:12:29.532 --> 00:12:31.265
For obvious reasons.

151
00:12:31.334 --> 00:12:34.635
your textbooks will
remain here in class.

152
00:12:34.704 --> 00:12:37.572
Parents tend to
be uncomfortable...

153
00:12:37.640 --> 00:12:40.441
with these sorts of images.

154
00:12:40.509 --> 00:12:44.412
Even biology can
be misunderstood.

155
00:12:44.480 --> 00:12:46.814
The point is...

156
00:12:46.883 --> 00:12:51.335
procreation is a beautiful...

157
00:12:51.404 --> 00:12:53.737
and blessed thing.

158
00:12:53.806 --> 00:12:55.806
And here in Wayward Pines.

159
00:12:57.160 --> 00:13:01.095
that really is your
most important job.

160
00:13:03.133 --> 00:13:04.865
Ben. Amy.

161
00:13:06.069 --> 00:13:08.269
Would you step up front. please?

162
00:13:08.705 --> 00:13:10.872
(Students Laughing)

163
00:13:10.940 --> 00:13:12.673
Come on. Quickly.

164
00:13:16.045 --> 00:13:17.811
Ah. behold...

165
00:13:17.880 --> 00:13:21.215
the male and the female.

166
00:13:22.152 --> 00:13:25.436
Two bodies
beautifully designed...

167
00:13:25.505 --> 00:13:27.972
to fit together.

168
00:13:28.041 --> 00:13:31.576
Effortlessly. seamlessly.

169
00:13:31.644 --> 00:13:35.813
Like two perfect puzzle
pieces. Like hand in glove.

170
00:13:35.881 --> 00:13:40.050
(Students Laughing) Yes. yes.
It's embarrassing to talk about.

171
00:13:40.119 --> 00:13:43.937
But... what if... What
if Ben was a bee...

172
00:13:44.006 --> 00:13:46.140
and Amy was a flower?

173
00:13:47.293 --> 00:13:49.733
Well. that wouldn't be
funny at all. would it?

174
00:13:53.216 --> 00:13:58.152
Wayward Pines needs
a new generation.

175
00:13:58.221 --> 00:14:01.939
And one day. not
too long from now.

176
00:14:02.008 --> 00:14:05.677
you all will have the honor...

177
00:14:05.745 --> 00:14:08.729
of parenting the
first generation...

178
00:14:09.332 --> 00:14:13.501
of 100% originals.

179
00:14:14.804 --> 00:14:17.872
Now take a look around
the room. (Students Snicker)

180
00:14:17.940 --> 00:14:20.675
This is a small town...
(Giggles) Right?

181
00:14:20.744 --> 00:14:26.647
Chances are your mate. your co-parent.
is sitting right here in this room.

182
00:14:26.716 --> 00:14:31.419
(Students Laugh) And it's part of
my job. as your teacher and counselor.

183
00:14:32.556 --> 00:14:34.772
to help you find each other.

184
00:14:35.625 --> 00:14:37.124
(Chuckles)

185
00:14:37.193 --> 00:14:39.042
You two may sit down.

186
00:14:40.546 --> 00:14:42.546
(Students Laughing)

187
00:14:50.440 --> 00:14:52.740
That was weird.

188
00:14:55.778 --> 00:14:59.780
♪♪ (Whistling "Twinkle.
Twinkle. Little Star")

189
00:15:02.118 --> 00:15:04.268
Ah! There you are.

190
00:15:04.336 --> 00:15:07.972
Nurse. could you give me a moment
alone with Dr. Jenkins. please?

191
00:15:08.041 --> 00:15:09.791
Thank you.

192
00:15:09.859 --> 00:15:11.859
Wonderful news.

193
00:15:11.928 --> 00:15:15.279
You know I'm doing my annual
fertility consults this morning.

194
00:15:15.348 --> 00:15:19.617
and already. two
new pregnancies.

195
00:15:20.837 --> 00:15:22.770
Imagine.

196
00:15:22.839 --> 00:15:26.006
two new members
of our first generation.

197
00:15:28.327 --> 00:15:30.645
That is wonderful.

198
00:15:31.481 --> 00:15:33.814
David. what is it?

199
00:15:35.968 --> 00:15:39.070
Why are they trying
to undermine us?

200
00:15:39.138 --> 00:15:42.823
Is it inevitable. this
passion for self-destruction?

201
00:15:42.892 --> 00:15:44.758
Have you eaten today?

202
00:15:45.345 --> 00:15:47.245
Pam.

203
00:15:47.313 --> 00:15:49.046
is it happening again?

204
00:15:49.115 --> 00:15:51.666
We always get like this.

205
00:15:51.735 --> 00:15:54.368
And you worry so.
and you forget to eat.

206
00:15:54.437 --> 00:15:58.622
And once your blood sugar drops.
the whole world looks gloomy. hmm?

207
00:16:00.293 --> 00:16:03.877
Ethan Burke will ferret
out these troublemakers.

208
00:16:05.214 --> 00:16:09.616
Sheriff Burke will
get us through this...

209
00:16:09.685 --> 00:16:12.052
present difficulty.

210
00:16:12.121 --> 00:16:13.871
That's very generous of you.

211
00:16:13.940 --> 00:16:17.809
Well. you believe in
him. I believe in him.

212
00:16:18.812 --> 00:16:21.478
Dr. Jenkins? Wayne
Johnson is here.

213
00:16:22.415 --> 00:16:24.248
Oh. thank you. Nurse. (Chuckles)

214
00:16:24.317 --> 00:16:26.050
Off to work.

215
00:16:27.553 --> 00:16:31.221
- Great news
about the pregnancies.
- Oh. indeed. (Chuckles)

216
00:16:54.563 --> 00:16:56.342
(Whispering) Just be
careful. All right. great.

217
00:16:56.366 --> 00:16:57.965
Okay. For sure.

218
00:16:58.034 --> 00:17:00.434
Yep. Bye-bye.

219
00:17:03.272 --> 00:17:04.838
Morning. Ethan.

220
00:17:06.125 --> 00:17:08.710
- Friend of yours?
- Oh. Franklin?

221
00:17:08.778 --> 00:17:10.945
Yeah. I mean. you
know. it's a small town.

222
00:17:11.014 --> 00:17:13.547
Yeah. you guys have been
seeing a lot of each other.

223
00:17:14.551 --> 00:17:16.445
I'm gonna need you
to come with me...

224
00:17:16.469 --> 00:17:19.220
so we can talk more privately.

225
00:17:19.288 --> 00:17:21.521
Sure. What about?

226
00:17:21.590 --> 00:17:24.542
About the damn bomb
in my truck. Harold.

227
00:17:26.613 --> 00:17:28.796
I didn't... I don't know
anything about this.

228
00:17:30.115 --> 00:17:32.616
Okay. Well. let's
go to my office.

229
00:17:32.685 --> 00:17:35.185
and you can tell me
about what you don't know.

230
00:17:44.313 --> 00:17:46.046
All right. let's go.

231
00:17:50.803 --> 00:17:52.820
(Tires Screech)

232
00:17:56.126 --> 00:17:58.592
Don't make me subdue
you again. Harold. (Groans)

233
00:17:58.661 --> 00:18:00.945
Next time I won't be so gentle.

234
00:18:01.014 --> 00:18:02.496
(Pants)

235
00:18:02.565 --> 00:18:04.998
That's okay. folks.
He tripped and fell.

236
00:18:05.068 --> 00:18:06.751
Let's go.

237
00:18:07.754 --> 00:18:09.419
(Exhales Sharply)

238
00:18:15.444 --> 00:18:18.045
Franklin made the bomb.

239
00:18:18.114 --> 00:18:22.333
And you. or somebody who
works for you. planted it in my truck.

240
00:18:22.402 --> 00:18:24.986
I swear. I don't know anything
about a bomb in your truck.

241
00:18:25.054 --> 00:18:28.122
But you know about the other
bombs that Franklin made...

242
00:18:28.190 --> 00:18:30.524
The ones that
are still out there.

243
00:18:30.593 --> 00:18:32.994
'Cause that's what
this is all about. isn't it?

244
00:18:33.062 --> 00:18:35.195
You want to take down the fence.

245
00:18:36.699 --> 00:18:39.133
Don't you want to get out?

246
00:18:39.201 --> 00:18:41.368
Just go somewhere. anywhere?

247
00:18:42.772 --> 00:18:45.439
There is no somewhere.
no anywhere.

248
00:18:48.077 --> 00:18:52.613
I want names... of
everybody in your group.

249
00:18:52.682 --> 00:18:54.515
starting with your leader.

250
00:18:55.118 --> 00:18:56.850
Who is he?

251
00:18:57.920 --> 00:19:00.321
Or maybe it's a she?

252
00:19:08.814 --> 00:19:10.714
There's no one else.

253
00:19:10.783 --> 00:19:13.217
Really? I acted alone.

254
00:19:13.286 --> 00:19:15.319
You acted alone. Mm-hmm.

255
00:19:15.388 --> 00:19:18.755
So that means that you did
plant the bomb in my truck.

256
00:19:18.824 --> 00:19:21.158
and you were lying about
it when you denied it.

257
00:19:21.227 --> 00:19:24.428
But you're telling me
the truth now. is that it?

258
00:19:24.496 --> 00:19:25.996
Great.

259
00:19:26.933 --> 00:19:28.432
(Groans)

260
00:19:37.143 --> 00:19:38.643
Okay.

261
00:19:39.762 --> 00:19:42.029
Give this to Kate.

262
00:19:42.097 --> 00:19:43.831
You can go now.

263
00:19:46.502 --> 00:19:48.542
Um. I don't
understand. I confessed.

264
00:19:48.571 --> 00:19:50.387
Yeah. I got it.

265
00:19:51.390 --> 00:19:52.873
Go.

266
00:20:05.704 --> 00:20:08.738
Mornin'. beautiful.
Sorry I'm late.

267
00:20:10.326 --> 00:20:13.060
I wish I could
blame it on the traffic.

268
00:20:13.129 --> 00:20:15.729
But somehow I don't
think that'll fly. (Chuckles)

269
00:20:15.798 --> 00:20:18.911
Good morning. You seem
like you're in a great mood.

270
00:20:18.935 --> 00:20:20.801
(Chuckles) Crispy
like a cracker.

271
00:20:20.869 --> 00:20:23.287
I passed by that lot
this morning. Plot 33.

272
00:20:24.207 --> 00:20:26.085
And I think I found something.

273
00:20:26.109 --> 00:20:29.893
There appears to be a substructure
of some kind. underneath the soil.

274
00:20:29.962 --> 00:20:33.981
- It felt like metal.
- Oh. a water tank maybe.

275
00:20:34.050 --> 00:20:36.867
(Stammering) But it's
buried in an empty lot. Bill.

276
00:20:36.936 --> 00:20:40.004
that wouldn't... Oh.
life's full of mysteries.

277
00:20:40.072 --> 00:20:42.284
all chock-full of
head-scratchers.

278
00:20:42.308 --> 00:20:44.875
I wouldn't think
about it too much.

279
00:20:44.944 --> 00:20:49.180
Besides. you really shouldn't
snoop around out there.

280
00:20:49.248 --> 00:20:50.981
And why is that?

281
00:20:57.907 --> 00:21:00.235
The secret to a safe
and happy town...

282
00:21:00.259 --> 00:21:02.570
is everyone minding
their own business.

283
00:21:02.594 --> 00:21:06.296
People need to do
what they're supposed to.

284
00:21:06.365 --> 00:21:08.260
And not do what they're not.

285
00:21:08.284 --> 00:21:09.984
Right. Now.

286
00:21:10.052 --> 00:21:14.755
uh. I need you to go down to the hospital
in a bit and pick up some files for me.

287
00:21:14.824 --> 00:21:16.824
If you're not too busy.

288
00:21:21.046 --> 00:21:22.529
(Knocking)

289
00:21:30.372 --> 00:21:33.407
I got your note. Came
as soon as I could.

290
00:21:34.210 --> 00:21:35.942
Good. Come on in.

291
00:21:37.179 --> 00:21:38.929
Here. sit down.

292
00:21:40.833 --> 00:21:45.068
Don't worry. I disabled
all the surveillance in here.

293
00:21:45.137 --> 00:21:47.204
I thought you didn't
care about that.

294
00:21:47.273 --> 00:21:49.824
It's not for my safety.

295
00:21:49.892 --> 00:21:51.992
Coffee?

296
00:21:52.061 --> 00:21:54.945
I heard about the
bomb in your truck.

297
00:21:55.013 --> 00:21:57.514
You have to believe me.
I-I don't know who did that.

298
00:21:57.583 --> 00:21:59.216
Good.

299
00:21:59.285 --> 00:22:03.137
But you can figure
out who did. can't you?

300
00:22:03.206 --> 00:22:05.039
Because you're their leader.

301
00:22:06.542 --> 00:22:10.160
- What if I was?
- Come on. Kate! Of course you are.

302
00:22:11.029 --> 00:22:12.562
Look. Harold was an accountant.

303
00:22:12.631 --> 00:22:16.634
If there's anybody leading
resistance in this town. it's not Harold.

304
00:22:16.702 --> 00:22:19.503
So who else is
involved in this group?

305
00:22:19.572 --> 00:22:23.607
This group is the only thing
that's kept me sane here.

306
00:22:23.675 --> 00:22:26.426
How long have you been active?

307
00:22:27.713 --> 00:22:30.114
It evolved over time.

308
00:22:30.183 --> 00:22:32.263
We started as something else.

309
00:22:32.318 --> 00:22:35.653
Just a few of us
trying to connect.

310
00:22:37.506 --> 00:22:41.308
We'd meet in secret. just
to be real with each other.

311
00:22:43.612 --> 00:22:47.147
Uh. Kate Hewson.

312
00:22:47.216 --> 00:22:49.450
Uh. Seattle.

313
00:22:49.518 --> 00:22:53.620
I miss the ferry boats. oysters.

314
00:22:53.689 --> 00:22:55.689
hiking Burroughs trail.

315
00:22:56.659 --> 00:22:58.291
my friends.

316
00:23:03.332 --> 00:23:05.932
I'm. uh... I'm-I'm Franklin.

317
00:23:06.001 --> 00:23:07.534
(Clears Throat)

318
00:23:07.603 --> 00:23:09.102
Uh...

319
00:23:11.240 --> 00:23:12.740
(Mutters)

320
00:23:13.843 --> 00:23:17.244
Um. Harold
Ballinger. Saint Paul.

321
00:23:17.946 --> 00:23:21.114
Um. I have a fiancée.

322
00:23:30.125 --> 00:23:32.359
How come you didn't
tell me any of this...

323
00:23:32.428 --> 00:23:34.177
when I first got here?

324
00:23:34.246 --> 00:23:37.247
Ethan. I've been
trapped here for 12 years.

325
00:23:37.316 --> 00:23:40.050
Try and imagine
what that's like.

326
00:23:40.119 --> 00:23:42.898
And then you show up. and
a week later you're sheriff?

327
00:23:42.922 --> 00:23:45.272
All right. look. It stops now.

328
00:23:45.341 --> 00:23:49.021
Why would I stop trying
to escape this prison?

329
00:23:50.813 --> 00:23:53.046
(Sighs) Look.

330
00:23:53.115 --> 00:23:55.115
The world that you and I knew.

331
00:23:55.184 --> 00:23:58.251
the world outside the
fence. that no longer exists.

332
00:23:58.320 --> 00:24:00.937
It's not 2014. it's not...

333
00:24:01.006 --> 00:24:04.375
It's not even the
21st century anymore.

334
00:24:04.443 --> 00:24:09.279
(Chuckles) What-What do you mean
it's not the 21st century anymore?

335
00:24:11.467 --> 00:24:12.967
(Sighs)

336
00:24:17.123 --> 00:24:19.123
Hey! Good class today.

337
00:24:19.191 --> 00:24:21.425
Oh. thanks. Amy. Yeah.

338
00:24:21.494 --> 00:24:25.129
You and Ben look so nice
together. How is that working out?

339
00:24:25.197 --> 00:24:27.597
It's great actually.

340
00:24:27.666 --> 00:24:30.767
I really like him. Like. a lot.

341
00:24:30.836 --> 00:24:33.203
(Chuckles) Oh. I'm so glad.

342
00:24:33.272 --> 00:24:38.108
As a teacher. it's so fulfilling when an
assignment turns into something more.

343
00:24:38.177 --> 00:24:41.211
Yeah. he's sweet. Kind of shy.

344
00:24:41.280 --> 00:24:43.514
I don't think he's
had much experience.

345
00:24:43.582 --> 00:24:46.050
You might be his
first real girlfriend.

346
00:24:48.187 --> 00:24:52.923
I was thinking of maybe
asking him out later tonight.

347
00:24:54.560 --> 00:24:58.162
Go someplace secluded
and romantic. Mmm.

348
00:24:58.230 --> 00:25:02.766
I just... I feel like I'm
ready for us to be more...

349
00:25:02.834 --> 00:25:04.501
intimate.

350
00:25:05.738 --> 00:25:08.105
(Megan) He's not pressuring you?

351
00:25:08.974 --> 00:25:11.709
Ben? Oh. God. no.

352
00:25:11.777 --> 00:25:14.278
I just hope I don't
have to pressure him.

353
00:25:14.346 --> 00:25:18.015
(Chuckling) I'm so happy
for you. Enjoy this moment.

354
00:25:18.083 --> 00:25:20.723
There's nothing like being young
and in love. (School Bell Ringing)

355
00:25:28.693 --> 00:25:30.472
(Kate) So let me
get this straight.

356
00:25:30.496 --> 00:25:34.281
Whoever's behind all this... the
people up there pulling the strings...

357
00:25:34.350 --> 00:25:36.583
You work for them now?

358
00:25:39.188 --> 00:25:40.704
(Sighs)

359
00:25:42.141 --> 00:25:45.976
Hand over whoever it was that
planted that bomb in my truck.

360
00:25:46.045 --> 00:25:48.795
surrender your arms and
explosives by tomorrow morning.

361
00:25:48.864 --> 00:25:51.881
and everything stays between us.

362
00:25:51.951 --> 00:25:54.251
You can't take down that fence.

363
00:25:56.188 --> 00:25:57.687
Okay.

364
00:26:01.042 --> 00:26:03.427
- (Door Closes)
- (Metal Clatters)

365
00:26:03.496 --> 00:26:07.147
(Footsteps)

366
00:26:07.216 --> 00:26:09.216
(Rhythmic Knocking)

367
00:26:22.998 --> 00:26:26.333
You were right.
They got to Ethan.

368
00:26:27.803 --> 00:26:29.836
We have to advance
the timetable.

369
00:26:31.056 --> 00:26:33.290
He knows about us.
He knows about Franklin.

370
00:26:33.359 --> 00:26:36.376
Exactly. We have a
very narrow window.

371
00:26:36.445 --> 00:26:38.244
We're not gonna
get a second chance.

372
00:26:39.197 --> 00:26:40.981
We have to tell everyone.

373
00:26:41.950 --> 00:26:43.950
We execute tonight.

374
00:26:44.019 --> 00:26:46.837
(Phone Ringing)

375
00:26:50.926 --> 00:26:53.493
Ballinger Toys.

376
00:26:53.562 --> 00:26:57.097
Oh! Well. hello. Pam.

377
00:26:57.166 --> 00:27:01.668
Of course. Uh. it slipped
my mind completely. (Laughs)

378
00:27:01.736 --> 00:27:04.104
We've been backlogged
with orders and...

379
00:27:04.173 --> 00:27:06.373
Is-Is it... Is it possible
to reschedule?

380
00:27:07.676 --> 00:27:10.077
Of course. I-I understand
the importance.

381
00:27:10.145 --> 00:27:12.245
Uh. we'll be right over.

382
00:27:12.314 --> 00:27:14.047
All right then.

383
00:27:16.185 --> 00:27:18.986
It's our annual
fertility consult.

384
00:27:19.721 --> 00:27:21.721
Of course it is. yeah.

385
00:27:21.790 --> 00:27:24.124
There's no point in
making her suspicious.

386
00:27:25.360 --> 00:27:27.320
(Sighs) Well...

387
00:27:29.064 --> 00:27:30.564
So...

388
00:27:32.668 --> 00:27:34.702
We have a married couple...

389
00:27:34.770 --> 00:27:37.904
Young. fertile.
in their prime...

390
00:27:37.973 --> 00:27:40.574
And yet somehow...

391
00:27:40.643 --> 00:27:42.376
not pregnant.

392
00:27:43.879 --> 00:27:45.778
Yeah. (Chuckles)

393
00:27:45.847 --> 00:27:47.981
(Pam) I don't understand it.

394
00:27:48.050 --> 00:27:49.844
Your lab work is all good.

395
00:27:49.868 --> 00:27:52.747
There's no problem with
the sperm count. Good.

396
00:27:52.771 --> 00:27:56.006
And you? Periods regular?

397
00:27:57.476 --> 00:28:00.076
Everything is in working
order. (Harold) Mm-hmm.

398
00:28:05.417 --> 00:28:08.902
Well. thanks so
much for coming in.

399
00:28:15.276 --> 00:28:18.895
You know. I've always thought
so highly of the two of you.

400
00:28:18.964 --> 00:28:21.498
Ever since I introduced you.

401
00:28:21.567 --> 00:28:25.052
- Hmm.
- I mean. what a blend
of genetics.

402
00:28:26.021 --> 00:28:28.588
The perfect Wayward
Pines couple.

403
00:28:28.657 --> 00:28:30.273
Don't let me down.

404
00:28:30.342 --> 00:28:34.728
<i>(Woman On PA) Pharmacy. pick up
line 1-2. Pharmacy. pick up line 1-2.</i>

405
00:28:34.797 --> 00:28:37.497
How much time do you
need to gather the team?

406
00:28:37.566 --> 00:28:39.433
Whatever you can give me.

407
00:28:39.501 --> 00:28:42.835
And get with Ted and set
the backup plan in motion.

408
00:28:42.904 --> 00:28:44.404
Wait.

409
00:28:45.240 --> 00:28:47.318
Do you think we need both?

410
00:28:47.342 --> 00:28:49.292
We're only gonna get one shot.

411
00:28:56.401 --> 00:28:57.901
(Elevator Bell Dings)

412
00:29:03.709 --> 00:29:05.208
(Dings)

413
00:29:13.668 --> 00:29:15.168
(Dings)

414
00:29:18.507 --> 00:29:21.641
Kate. Do you have a minute?

415
00:29:22.878 --> 00:29:25.779
I'm very worried about Ethan.

416
00:29:27.649 --> 00:29:30.249
- Come on.
- Okay.

417
00:29:31.971 --> 00:29:35.105
(Kate) Did he tell you the story
about it being 2.000 years in the future?

418
00:29:35.174 --> 00:29:38.141
How the world is destroyed
and we're the only humans left?

419
00:29:39.361 --> 00:29:42.462
What is going on? I don't know.

420
00:29:42.530 --> 00:29:46.499
But I think they have some way of
brainwashing people up on that mountain.

421
00:29:46.568 --> 00:29:48.328
You know. I...
Okay. there's more.

422
00:29:48.370 --> 00:29:50.938
(Sighs) The week
after I got here.

423
00:29:51.006 --> 00:29:52.884
I finally found a
phone that worked.

424
00:29:52.908 --> 00:29:55.442
I called a secure line
belonging to the Service.

425
00:29:55.510 --> 00:29:57.438
and Agent Hassler
left me a message.

426
00:29:57.462 --> 00:29:58.773
Adam Hassler? Mm-hmm.

427
00:29:58.797 --> 00:30:00.280
What did he say?

428
00:30:00.349 --> 00:30:02.882
That I was entering a
government experiment.

429
00:30:02.951 --> 00:30:06.119
That I should lay low. blend in.

430
00:30:06.188 --> 00:30:08.555
and that I may
be severely tested.

431
00:30:08.624 --> 00:30:10.657
possibly by another agent.

432
00:30:10.725 --> 00:30:13.176
You think that Ethan
is... I-I don't know.

433
00:30:13.245 --> 00:30:14.978
But I can't rule it out.

434
00:30:15.047 --> 00:30:18.815
Theresa. you know Hassler. He
is nothing if not a straight shooter.

435
00:30:18.884 --> 00:30:20.667
How much of this
have you told Ethan?

436
00:30:20.736 --> 00:30:24.237
I haven't. and I'm not
sure it's a good idea to.

437
00:30:24.306 --> 00:30:26.106
(Chattering In Distance)

438
00:30:26.175 --> 00:30:27.908
I really have to go.

439
00:30:36.584 --> 00:30:38.363
You're a good person. Theresa.

440
00:30:38.387 --> 00:30:42.139
And I wish we had met
under different circumstances.

441
00:30:43.075 --> 00:30:45.508
I'm so sorry.

442
00:30:49.147 --> 00:30:52.149
- Ethan. we're worried
about you.
- You're worried about me?

443
00:30:52.217 --> 00:30:54.117
Yes.

444
00:30:54.186 --> 00:30:56.686
What. do you think
this is all in my head?

445
00:30:56.755 --> 00:30:58.766
(Scoffs) What do you
think... You think. uh.

446
00:30:58.790 --> 00:31:00.523
I was brainwashed?

447
00:31:00.592 --> 00:31:02.326
I saw stuff out there. Theresa.

448
00:31:02.394 --> 00:31:05.111
I'm not making this up.
Everything I told you is true.

449
00:31:05.180 --> 00:31:07.620
But you're telling me
that everything is gone.

450
00:31:08.383 --> 00:31:10.650
Except us.

451
00:31:10.719 --> 00:31:13.019
And I want to keep it that way.

452
00:31:13.088 --> 00:31:16.656
So. please. tell me.
what else did she say?

453
00:31:16.725 --> 00:31:20.610
She told me not to tell you
anything. and then she left.

454
00:31:20.679 --> 00:31:23.091
She was very emotional
when she said good-bye.

455
00:31:23.115 --> 00:31:25.966
like it was a
permanent good-bye.

456
00:31:28.437 --> 00:31:31.805
- Where's Ben?
- He's at school.

457
00:31:32.858 --> 00:31:35.091
Okay. I'm gonna go get him.

458
00:31:35.160 --> 00:31:37.143
I think they're
planning something.

459
00:31:40.883 --> 00:31:42.915
Hey. so I was thinking.

460
00:31:42.984 --> 00:31:47.420
How about later tonight. you and I
sneak out for a walk in the woods?

461
00:31:47.489 --> 00:31:50.235
(Chuckles) Isn't that...
against the rules?

462
00:31:50.259 --> 00:31:53.260
Well. there are rules
and then there are rules.

463
00:31:53.328 --> 00:31:55.378
There's a sweet spot I've
been meaning to show you.

464
00:31:55.447 --> 00:31:58.247
It's like a little
meadow up in the trees.

465
00:31:59.985 --> 00:32:02.465
How would we get there?

466
00:32:04.973 --> 00:32:07.324
I have a plan.

467
00:32:07.393 --> 00:32:09.226
Meet me after dinner?

468
00:32:09.294 --> 00:32:11.027
Corner of Birch and Ninth?

469
00:32:11.797 --> 00:32:13.917
Yeah. sure. (Chuckles)

470
00:32:15.266 --> 00:32:18.201
It was fun in class today. huh?

471
00:32:18.269 --> 00:32:21.971
I don't understand why people
get so nervous talking about biology.

472
00:32:22.040 --> 00:32:25.074
(Stammering)
Yeah. I know. right?

473
00:32:25.143 --> 00:32:27.344
- It's just nature.
- (Ethan) Ben!

474
00:32:29.013 --> 00:32:31.614
- One second.
- (Sighs)

475
00:32:32.884 --> 00:32:35.836
What? Look. I'm gonna
need you to come home.

476
00:32:35.904 --> 00:32:38.738
I'm kind of busy right now.

477
00:32:38.807 --> 00:32:40.306
Oh. hi.

478
00:32:40.375 --> 00:32:42.375
I'll explain it to
you in the car.

479
00:32:42.444 --> 00:32:44.677
Say good-bye. Come on. Dad.

480
00:32:44.746 --> 00:32:47.464
Amy. I'm terribly sorry.
but Ben's gotta come home.

481
00:32:47.533 --> 00:32:49.444
Okay. He'll talk to you later.

482
00:32:49.468 --> 00:32:51.201
Go ahead. say good-bye.

483
00:32:54.806 --> 00:32:56.540
Sorry. I gotta go.

484
00:32:56.608 --> 00:32:59.192
It's okay. Meet me later.

485
00:33:02.864 --> 00:33:04.364
(Sighs)

486
00:33:04.966 --> 00:33:06.633
(Engine Starts)

487
00:33:17.796 --> 00:33:19.440
(Harold) I just need to know.

488
00:33:19.464 --> 00:33:22.949
Did you put that pipe bomb in
the sheriff's truck this morning?

489
00:33:25.754 --> 00:33:28.321
Damn it. Ted. The
last thing we need...

490
00:33:28.390 --> 00:33:31.090
is him breathing down our
necks. We're not murderers.

491
00:33:31.159 --> 00:33:34.444
Why not? They murder.

492
00:33:34.512 --> 00:33:36.913
You've been to your
share of reckonings.

493
00:33:42.054 --> 00:33:44.754
Do you want me
to do this or not?

494
00:34:28.817 --> 00:34:31.951
<i>(Pam On Comm Link) Second
camera just went out in Zone 33.</i>

495
00:34:32.020 --> 00:34:34.120
(Ethan) No. it's Kate.
She's trying to throw us off.

496
00:34:35.323 --> 00:34:37.823
(Electricity Crackling)

497
00:34:40.679 --> 00:34:43.263
We got 10 minutes till
the guards circle around.

498
00:34:43.332 --> 00:34:46.065
And once that fence is
breached. there's no turning back.

499
00:34:46.134 --> 00:34:48.301
They'll be on us fast.

500
00:34:49.404 --> 00:34:52.271
<i>(Beeping)</i>

501
00:34:52.340 --> 00:34:54.140
(Ethan) Where
are the blind spots?

502
00:34:54.209 --> 00:34:56.876
<i>(Pam) There's one at
Zone 41. Right at the fence.</i>

503
00:34:56.945 --> 00:34:58.489
(Ethan) Almost there.

504
00:34:58.513 --> 00:35:00.780
So if anyone's having
second thoughts.

505
00:35:00.848 --> 00:35:02.515
now is the time
to go. all right?

506
00:35:02.584 --> 00:35:05.585
(Ethan) Okay. that's it.
Everybody stay right where you are!

507
00:35:05.653 --> 00:35:07.620
- Down on the ground!
- Ethan...

508
00:35:07.689 --> 00:35:10.169
I'm not letting you
blow up that fence.

509
00:35:10.342 --> 00:35:12.608
Get down on the ground!

510
00:35:13.212 --> 00:35:15.212
Okay. Franklin.

511
00:35:15.280 --> 00:35:17.047
Disarm that bomb.

512
00:35:18.083 --> 00:35:19.816
Don't do it.

513
00:35:21.436 --> 00:35:24.516
Disarm the bomb.
or she's dead. No.

514
00:35:26.040 --> 00:35:27.773
(Whispering) No. Franklin.

515
00:35:33.598 --> 00:35:35.126
(Hammer Cocks) (Kate) No.

516
00:35:35.150 --> 00:35:36.883
(Kate Breathing Rapidly)

517
00:35:46.327 --> 00:35:48.061
(Device Powering Down)

518
00:35:51.450 --> 00:35:54.317
I trusted you. Let's go.

519
00:35:55.820 --> 00:35:57.940
Come on. On your feet.

520
00:35:58.623 --> 00:36:00.123
Let's go.

521
00:36:04.579 --> 00:36:06.095
(Lock Clicks)

522
00:36:09.551 --> 00:36:11.568
(Keys Jangling)

523
00:36:15.907 --> 00:36:17.406
(Lock Clicks)

524
00:36:24.366 --> 00:36:26.115
We had a deal. Kate.

525
00:36:26.184 --> 00:36:30.820
They did something to you. Ethan.
You just don't know it. You'll see.

526
00:36:30.889 --> 00:36:32.872
Very soon. we will
be back in Seattle.

527
00:36:32.940 --> 00:36:35.260
overlooking that bay...
Seattle? No. forget it. Kate.

528
00:36:35.310 --> 00:36:37.109
That's not gonna happen.

529
00:36:37.178 --> 00:36:40.964
You've got to convince these
people to stop this insanity.

530
00:36:42.333 --> 00:36:44.050
It's not gonna stop.

531
00:36:45.920 --> 00:36:48.437
It's just begun.

532
00:36:51.893 --> 00:36:53.859
Where's your husband?

533
00:36:56.298 --> 00:36:58.732
There's another bomb.

534
00:36:58.800 --> 00:37:01.434
It's a backup.

535
00:37:01.503 --> 00:37:03.386
Where's Harold. Kate?

536
00:37:05.707 --> 00:37:07.724
Where's Harold?

537
00:38:03.932 --> 00:38:05.448
<i>(Amy) Should be here any second.</i>

538
00:38:05.517 --> 00:38:09.185
It's always right on
time. right at 8:00.

539
00:38:09.254 --> 00:38:11.987
We can catch a
ride up to the pines.

540
00:38:12.057 --> 00:38:15.808
Uh. we could just
walk. (Chuckles)

541
00:38:15.877 --> 00:38:17.610
It's more fun this way.

542
00:38:18.212 --> 00:38:19.712
(Brakes Squeal)

543
00:38:19.781 --> 00:38:23.382
Just relax. newbie. Done
this plenty of other times.

544
00:39:25.613 --> 00:39:27.613
(Ethan) I need you
to locate Harold.

545
00:39:27.682 --> 00:39:29.460
(Clears Throat) (Typing)

546
00:39:29.484 --> 00:39:31.217
<i>(Computers Whirring)</i>

547
00:39:31.286 --> 00:39:33.018
Harold Ballinger.

548
00:39:36.540 --> 00:39:38.258
Last seen at the Biergarten.

549
00:39:38.326 --> 00:39:40.059
Less than an hour ago.

550
00:39:42.430 --> 00:39:44.813
- Who's that?
- That's...

551
00:39:44.882 --> 00:39:46.882
<i>(Computer Whirring)</i>

552
00:39:47.752 --> 00:39:49.785
Ted Laufer.

553
00:39:49.854 --> 00:39:52.906
He drives the delivery truck.

554
00:39:52.974 --> 00:39:54.874
Where is the truck now?

555
00:39:54.943 --> 00:39:57.343
Well. he takes the
same route every day.

556
00:39:57.412 --> 00:40:01.548
Finishes up on 16. Heads
up Main to Access 1.

557
00:40:01.616 --> 00:40:03.899
Drops off the truck. and
then picks up another one.

558
00:40:03.968 --> 00:40:05.868
And where does he
switch the two trucks?

559
00:40:05.937 --> 00:40:07.670
At the fence.

560
00:40:13.044 --> 00:40:14.928
What's that?

561
00:40:15.730 --> 00:40:18.064
(Typing)

562
00:41:05.430 --> 00:41:07.430
♪♪ (Music Box)

563
00:41:09.067 --> 00:41:10.800
What's that?

564
00:41:19.026 --> 00:41:21.026
♪♪ (Continues)

565
00:41:30.272 --> 00:41:32.272
♪♪ (Continues)

566
00:41:53.561 --> 00:41:55.061
(Tires Squealing)

567
00:41:56.797 --> 00:41:59.558
(Harold) Here he comes.
We gotta slow him down.

568
00:42:05.507 --> 00:42:07.723
(Tires Screeching)

569
00:42:10.345 --> 00:42:13.379
(Man Groaning)

570
00:42:13.448 --> 00:42:15.548
(Harold) Get up. Get up.

571
00:42:15.617 --> 00:42:17.966
(Grunting)

572
00:42:18.035 --> 00:42:20.035
(Hissing)

573
00:42:25.944 --> 00:42:29.094
♪♪ (Music Box)

574
00:42:41.960 --> 00:42:43.959
(Brakes Squeal)

575
00:42:48.883 --> 00:42:50.399
♪♪ (Stops)

576
00:42:55.022 --> 00:42:57.022
(Amy Groaning)

577
00:43:01.229 --> 00:43:03.229
Are you okay? (Groans)

578
00:43:06.067 --> 00:43:07.366
Amy.

579
00:43:08.236 --> 00:43:10.316
Amy. what are you doing here?

580
00:43:18.746 --> 00:43:20.612
Ben?

581
00:43:26.937 --> 00:43:28.437
Ben!
